cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper investigates the scaling properties of Recurrent Neural Network Language Models (RNNLMs) and discusses language modeling benchmarks. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses training large RNNs and addresses questions related to model size, training-set size, computational costs, and memory. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as RNNLMs are a type of AI model used for natural language processing tasks. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper discusses the use of neural networks, specifically RNNs, for language modeling. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely category as the paper does not explicitly discuss computer vision or pattern recognition, but RNNs are also used in these fields and the paper may touch on related topics.
